      <p>
        Hints: Make sure you follow the proof format.
        You can use the hint to write the story.
        First, explain why the answer is <m>\binom{n}{k}</m>.
        Next, follow the hint to break it into cases.
        Explain why one case gives
        <m>\binom{n-1}{k-1}</m> and why the other case gives <m>\binom{n-1}{k}</m>.
      </p>
